#. <section class="sutta" id="sn42.3"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn42.3:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 42"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 42"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.3:0.2"
msgid "1. Gāmaṇivagga"
msgstr "1. Chiefs"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn42.3:0.3"
msgid "3. Yodhājīvasutta"
msgstr "3. A Warrior"

# I don’t think BB’s “mercenary” catches the name here. A mercenary is someone who fights for money, not principles, but this is just a professional soldier, in modern times, any soldier (as opposed to reservists, say)
#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn42.3:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho yodhājīvo gāmaṇi yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā … pe … "
"ekamantaṃ nisinno kho yodhājīvo gāmaṇi bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Dustin the warrior chief went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one "
"side, and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn42.3:1.2"
msgid ""
"“sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante, pubbakānaṃ ācariyapācariyānaṃ yodhājīvānaṃ "
"bhāsamānānaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, I have heard that the warriors of the past who were teachers of "
"teachers said:"

msgctxt "sn42.3:1.3"
msgid ""
"‘yo so yodhājīvo saṅgāme ussahati vāyamati, tamenaṃ ussahantaṃ vāyamantaṃ "
"pare hananti pariyāpādenti, so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā parajitānaṃ "
"devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Suppose a warrior, while striving and struggling in battle, is killed and "
"finished off by his foes. When his body breaks up, after death, he’s reborn "
"in the company of the gods of the fallen.’"

msgctxt "sn42.3:1.4"
msgid "Idha bhagavā kimāhā”ti?"
msgstr "What does the Buddha say about this?”"

msgctxt "sn42.3:1.5"
msgid "“Alaṃ, gāmaṇi, tiṭṭhatetaṃ; mā maṃ etaṃ pucchī”ti."
msgstr "“Enough, chief, let it be. Don’t ask me that.”"

msgctxt "sn42.3:1.6"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho … pe …"
msgstr "For a second time …"

msgctxt "sn42.3:1.7"
msgid "tatiyampi kho yodhājīvo gāmaṇi bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "And for a third time the warrior chief said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn42.3:1.8"
msgid ""
"“sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante, pubbakānaṃ ācariyapācariyānaṃ yodhājīvānaṃ "
"bhāsamānānaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, I have heard that the warriors of the past who were teachers of "
"teachers said:"

msgctxt "sn42.3:1.9"
msgid ""
"‘yo so yodhājīvo saṅgāme ussahati vāyamati, tamenaṃ ussahantaṃ vāyamantaṃ "
"pare hananti pariyāpādenti, so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā parajitānaṃ "
"devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Suppose a warrior, while striving and struggling in battle, is killed and "
"finished off by his foes. When his body breaks up, after death, he’s reborn "
"in the company of the gods of the fallen.’"

msgctxt "sn42.3:1.10"
msgid "Idha bhagavā kimāhā”ti?"
msgstr "What does the Buddha say about this?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.309"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn42.3:2.1"
msgid "“Addhā kho tyāhaṃ, gāmaṇi, na labhāmi:"
msgstr "“Clearly, chief, I’m not getting through to you when I say:"

msgctxt "sn42.3:2.2"
msgid "‘alaṃ, gāmaṇi, tiṭṭhatetaṃ; mā maṃ etaṃ pucchī’ti."
msgstr "‘Enough, chief, let it be. Don’t ask me that.’"

msgctxt "sn42.3:2.3"
msgid "Api ca tyāhaṃ byākarissāmi."
msgstr "Nevertheless, I will answer you."

#. VAR: gahitaṃ → hīnaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn42.3:2.4"
msgid ""
"Yo so, gāmaṇi, yodhājīvo saṅgāme ussahati vāyamati, tassa taṃ cittaṃ pubbe "
"gahitaṃ dukkaṭaṃ duppaṇihitaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"When a warrior strives and struggles in battle, their mind is already low, "
"degraded, and misdirected as they think:"

msgctxt "sn42.3:2.5"
msgid ""
"‘ime sattā haññantu vā bajjhantu vā ucchijjantu vā vinassantu vā mā vā "
"ahesuṃ iti vā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘May these sentient beings be killed, slaughtered, slain, destroyed, or "
"annihilated!’"

msgctxt "sn42.3:2.6"
msgid "Tamenaṃ ussahantaṃ vāyamantaṃ pare hananti pariyāpādenti;"
msgstr "His foes kill him and finish him off, and"

msgctxt "sn42.3:2.7"
msgid "so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā parajito nāma nirayo tattha upapajjatīti."
msgstr ""
"when his body breaks up, after death, he’s reborn in the hell called ‘The "
"Fallen’."

msgctxt "sn42.3:2.8"
msgid "Sace kho panassa evaṃ diṭṭhi hoti:"
msgstr "But if you have such a view:"

msgctxt "sn42.3:2.9"
msgid ""
"‘yo so yodhājīvo saṅgāme ussahati vāyamati tamenaṃ ussahantaṃ vāyamantaṃ "
"pare hananti pariyāpādenti, so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā parajitānaṃ "
"devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī’ti, sāssa hoti micchādiṭṭhi."
msgstr ""
"‘Suppose a warrior, while striving and struggling in battle, is killed and "
"finished off by his foes. When his body breaks up, after death, he’s reborn "
"in the company of the gods of the fallen.’ This is your wrong view."

msgctxt "sn42.3:2.10"
msgid ""
"Micchādiṭṭhikassa kho panāhaṃ, gāmaṇi, purisapuggalassa dvinnaṃ gatīnaṃ "
"aññataraṃ gatiṃ vadāmi—"
msgstr "An individual with wrong view is reborn in one of two places, I say:"

msgctxt "sn42.3:2.11"
msgid "nirayaṃ vā tiracchānayoniṃ vā”ti."
msgstr "hell or the animal realm.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn42.3:3.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, yodhājīvo gāmaṇi parodi, assūni pavattesi."
msgstr ""
"When he said this, Dustin the warrior chief cried and burst out in tears."

msgctxt "sn42.3:3.2"
msgid "“Etaṃ kho tyāhaṃ, gāmaṇi, nālatthaṃ:"
msgstr "“This is what I didn’t get through to you when I said:"

msgctxt "sn42.3:3.3"
msgid "‘alaṃ, gāmaṇi, tiṭṭhatetaṃ; mā maṃ etaṃ pucchī’”ti."
msgstr "‘Enough, chief, let it be. Don’t ask me that.’”"

msgctxt "sn42.3:3.4"
msgid "“Nāhaṃ, bhante, etaṃ rodāmi yaṃ maṃ bhagavā evamāha;"
msgstr "“Sir, I’m not crying because of what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn42.3:3.5"
msgid ""
"api cāhaṃ, bhante, pubbakehi ācariyapācariyehi yodhājīvehi dīgharattaṃ "
"nikato vañcito paluddho:"
msgstr ""
"But sir, for a long time I’ve been cheated, tricked, and deceived by the "
"warriors of the past who were teachers of teachers, who said:"

msgctxt "sn42.3:3.6"
msgid ""
"‘yo so yodhājīvo saṅgāme ussahati vāyamati, tamenaṃ ussahantaṃ vāyamantaṃ "
"pare hananti pariyāpādenti, so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā parajitānaṃ "
"devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Suppose a warrior, while striving and struggling in battle, is killed and "
"finished off by his foes. When his body breaks up, after death, he’s reborn "
"in the company of the gods of the fallen.’"

# punctuation incorrect
msgctxt "sn42.3:3.7"
msgid "“Abhikkantaṃ, bhante … pe …"
msgstr "Excellent, sir! Excellent! …"

msgctxt "sn42.3:3.8"
msgid "ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has "
"gone for refuge for life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn42.3:3.9"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
